title: For Sale:  Silencerco Osprey 9mm
postcontent: Silencerco Osprey 9mm with 1/2-28 piston - $719.95 Silencerco's Osprey family of pistol suppressors (or silencers, as often called) is a perfect blend of form and function.With the modern combat handgun in mind, Silencerco set out to create a silencer that performs well and looks like it belongs, the best possible marriage between host weapon and silencer. Silencerco went to work to make a suppressor that maximizes sound suppression levels, allows the use of more host pistols with factory sights, and has more operationally friendly features. What was created was the Osprey pistol silencer available for 9mm, .40 S&W, and 45ACP.Although round silencers are very effective for many applications, for a centerfire handgun round it has its limits. To obtain the most suppression, silencers must have as much internal volume as possible; but for a round tubular silencer, the only way to acquire more internal volume is by increasing the overall diameter and/or length. Increasing a tube's diameter will obscure the site picture of the host gun and inhibit the possibility of holstering a weapon with the silencer still attached to the host gun.The Osprey is an eccentric silencer, which means that the bore does not run down the middle of the tube. Because of this eccentric design, most of the baffles and internal volume is beneath the centerline of the bore and out of the way of the gun's sights, thus leaving the shooter the ability to use factory sights with little or no sight or target obstruction. The Osprey has flat side walls and angled edges that mimic many modern combat handgun slides and is just slightly wider than most host pistols. This feature allows the host weapon to be holstered with many popular open bottom holster designs with Osprey attached. The Osprey contains approximately 30% more internal volume than a traditional round tube silencer at the same length, but does so without obscuring the shooter's sight picture or adding excessive width and length.

title: For Sale/Trade:  OBO Yugo Mauser 24/47 all matching with Royal Yugo and German markings
postcontent:
Up for sale is a Yugoslavian Mauser Model 24/47. This rifle is all matching numbers to include the receiver, barrel, stock, bolt and magazine (magazine is a forced match, the others are not).

This is not a Mitchell Mauser. It is import stamped.

Previous arsenal and manufacture markings were scrubbed on this one, but are still visible.
Faintly below the 24/47 markings Royal Yugo markings can be seen, as well as the location of original manufacture (Artillery Technical Institute). This makes original manufacture prewar (1928-31). Hard to get a picture of this as it is so faint, but it is there and I certainly welcome anyone to inspect it in person if they wish.

There are also two scrubbed German acceptance stamps, one on the receiver, indicating that the action (not the rifle as it sits today) was seized and put into German service, and one on the bolt release. So the action certainly saw combat during WWII.

The rifling is nearly flawless. The rifle does have some surface rust on the receiver, but this is limited and there is no corrosion. Not pretty but this rifle has been through a lot looking at the number/type of arsenal marks and stock markings.

Cycles great, shoots/groups dead on (though I don't have anywhere to shoot long range, so a little high at 100 yards as expected).

I have taken pictures of the rifle in and out, including all the markings should anyone wish to see more, ask questions etc.

All and all would make an all matching good shooter with a little bit of history behind it.

(Source for manufacture date/location)
http://candrsenal.com/rifle-serbian-mauser-model-1924/

title: For Sale:  BRNO model 1 .22 LR
postcontent: Thanks for checking out my posting! I have a quite rare BRNO model 1 in .22LR  for sale. The condition shows use, and the metal has some pitting especially around the wood line. Bore seems to be in good shape however. Wood is dinged up with some scratches and dents, but nothing you wouldn't expect in a rifle this age. Has a magazine, but my bet is this is not the original magazine. It is missing the front sling swivel, the hood for the front sight, and the factory original butt plate. There is a cork butt plate that someone made for the gun, I'm assuming to lengthen the stock a bit. It's done quite well actually, and sort of looks like it honestly could have come from the factory that way if you didn't know better! Overall, I would rate the condition 85-89% It's not a prize collector, but because they are so rare, even in the condition it's in, it's still fairly nice and a great shooter grade Model 1 for sure. Would prefer Wi sales only, but shipping to FFL is not completely out of the question. Can send more pictures if interested. Price is $325.00

title: For Sale:  NIB CZ Custom Accu Shadow BLK #91735
postcontent:
This is a new-in-box, unfired pistol. Between the time I ordered it and the time it was ready in May, I had surgery on my trigger finger. It has not healed well enough to use this kind of high-quality competition pistol, plus I could use the cash.  This is the #91735 version with the match barrel, not one of the other ones.

NO TRADES!! Forgive me if I sound harsh, but I do a lot buying and selling online and there are quite a few folks out there who either cannot read or are simply knuckleheads.  So, you either have the money to buy this kind of gun or you don't.  I am of course okay if you don't, but please don't waste my time and yours with offers - if this is not worth the price to you, please just keep looking, and please don't send me silly emails.  I did actually lower the price, but I also have patience and am well aware of the demand for this gun,  I sold another I had last year for $2300.  Given the demand and supply, this is a very good price.  Thanks to those who do have a head on your shoulders for your understanding.

CZC ACCU Shadow  (CZC Custom Version with Match Fit Barrel)
CZC MATCH BARREL & FIXED SIGHT

CZC 75 SP01 ACCU Shadow #91735
USPSA Production Approved!
Features
*CZC Fitted Match Barrel
*CZC Stainless steel barrel bushing.
*CZC Stainless steel reverse plug.
*CZC SHORT reset trigger system “CZC SRTS”
*CZC Competition Fixed rear sight.

These modifications have been added to the already customized CZ Custom SP01 Shadow Pistol. #91029

We have been very busy at the CZ Custom Shop over the last few months. We have been working and perfecting some new products and parts for the SP01 Shadow and the CZ 75 Shadow. This details the changes brought about to create the CZ 75 SP01 ACCU SHADOW.

Let’s talk about the difference

We have hand fitted the "Made in the USA" CZC Match Grade Barrel, tighter fit and tolerance then standard factory barrel.

The new barrel bushing is threaded into the slide; the bushing is fitted to the barrel creating far less play than the current bushing system. The bushing also retains the new stainless steel guide plug.

The bushing keeps the front sight in the slide so no pin is necessary or needed (fitting the pin will damage the bushing threads.)

The bushing will need to be removed before the barrel can be taken from the gun.

Ransom Rest testing at 50 yards with Fiocchi 125 JHP (A ZERO bullet) has proved group of less than 3” compared with a factory new gun at about 5.0”. At 25 yards the groups were around 1.2” a one-hole group.

This can be retrofitted by CZC to any CZ with a full width slide.


What’s new and very exciting is the CZC SHRT reset trigger system. People have been asking for a shorter faster reset without the trigger swinging all the way forward in SA mode, now we have it.

We have taken almost all of the forward movement out of the single action position with the trigger moving on average less than a 1/16 (0.0625”) before stopping. We have basically created a 1911 single action on a double action gun.
